tldr: The user requested to add a database, admin dashboard, and authentication
  to a sleep questionnaire application based on a Statement of Work. The agent
  implemented a PostgreSQL database with Prisma, created API endpoints for
  questionnaire responses and CSV export, and built a simple admin dashboard
  with middleware-based password authentication.
overview: The user's intent was to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  adding persistent data storage, an administrative interface, and secure
  access. The agent evaluated the existing codebase, identified missing
  components, and developed a plan. Key decisions included using NeonDB
  (PostgreSQL) with Prisma for the database, implementing a simple
  password-based authentication, and building a basic admin dashboard. The
  approach involved updating demographic fields, creating a
   Prisma model, developing API routes for data
  submission, retrieval, and CSV export, and integrating Next.js middleware for
  authentication. The initial custom session management was simplified to a more
  straightforward cookie-based approach. The outcome is a fully functional
  backend for data management and a secure, accessible admin dashboard, with all
  components thoroughly tested.
